# opening
1. first time launch osc will store account info in .oscrc file
2. se co ls(-e: list all) repos up(fetch new) bco pull
3. A D !(lost) ?(non-exist before)
4. default: obs
5. osc

# modify package
osc log
osc diff
osc diff -r 2:33
osc status
osc revert .

# afternoon
osc add
osc rm 
osc ar
osc vc (to change log)
osc commit (-m)
### .oscrc
osc bl (build log)
osc repos: list repos per arch for current project 
osc r (result): project package rpm
osc getbinaries repo arch 

### summit to remote 
osc sr (submitrequest): source and target
osc my pkg (rq)
osc whois XJin

### local build
package path to see maintainer

### branch action
osc rdelete
osc rdiff
osc rebuild

osc sm (search maintainer): filter just the package in project which is still maintained


# 20150916 (rpm spec for rpmbuild or osc)
1. /etc/rpm/macro
2. rpm -ql rpm |grep macro
3. https://en.opensuse.org/openSUSE:Specfile_guidelines


# create patch
1. diff
2. git
3. git am 
4. base 64 coding for offline-imap: mutt plugin could apply patch directly from email (not save it in 
5. quilt tool for patch management)
